gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 127, Timberwolves 113
gameRecap.excerpt: Joel Embiid put up a season-high 51 points, along with 12 rebounds for the 76ers as they defeated the Timberwolves, 127-113. This is Embiid's 2nd 50+ point game of the season, and 7th of his career. Tyrese Maxey added 35 points and five 3PM for the 76ers in the victory, while Anthony Edwards (27 points, seven rebounds, five assists) and Karl-Anthony Towns (23 points, 13 rebounds) combined for 50 points for the Timberwolves in the losing effort. The 76ers improve to 19-8 on the season, while the Timberwolves fall to 20-6.
